    "sections": {
        "description": "<p><strong>NOTE: This block plugin is only compatible with hybrid and block themes.</strong></p>\n<p>The card block can be used as a content container with custom controls for padding, margin, background color/gradient and, hence the name of the block &#8211; box shadow.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin files to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/card-block-with-box-shadow</code> directory, or install the plugin through the WordPress plugins screen directly.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Go to WordPress block editor in page/post and type &#8220;/card&#8221; to choose the Card Block with Box Shadow block and begin editting.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='what%20type%20of%20blocks%20can%20be%20used%20inside%20the%20card%20block%20with%20box%20shadow%20block%3F'>\nWhat type of blocks can be used inside the Card Block with Box Shadow block?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Any block</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>2.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Refactor codebase to TypeScript</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
